/* --------------------- README (quick start) --------------------- */
/*
1) Create a folder, paste the files above into the same folder structure (models/, routes/, middleware/ and top-level files).
2) Copy .env.example -> .env and set values (MONGO_URI, JWT_SECRET, PORT, FRONTEND_URL, ALLOW_REGISTRATION)
3) npm install
4) npm run dev   (or npm start)
5) To pre-populate your profile and data run: npm run seed

API overview (all api paths are prefixed by /api):
- POST /api/auth/register   { name, email, password }
- POST /api/auth/login      { email, password } -> returns { token }
- GET  /api/profile         (Authorization: Bearer <token>) returns { user, projects, skills }
- PUT  /api/profile         (Authorization) update profile fields

Projects
- GET  /api/projects
- POST /api/projects        { title, description, projectDescription, technologies, image }
- PUT  /api/projects/:id
- DELETE /api/projects/:id

Skills
- GET  /api/skills
- POST /api/skills          { category, iconName, items }
- PUT  /api/skills/:id
- DELETE /api/skills/:id

Security notes:
- Registration can be disabled by setting ALLOW_REGISTRATION=false in .env
- Passwords are stored hashed (bcrypt). JWT tokens are used for auth in Authorization header.
*/
